Sentencas: Cobalt coatings are candidates to inhibit high-temperature surface oxidation of solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) stainless steel (SS) interconnects.
Titulo: The influence of pre-treatment on the oxidation behavior of Co coated SOFC interconnects

Sentencas: This study investigates the influence of surface pre-treatment on the oxidation behavior of cobalt coated SS441.
Titulo: The influence of pre-treatment on the oxidation behavior of Co coated SOFC interconnects

Sentencas: Metallic cobalt was deposited via DC magnetron sputtering on SS that had been pre-oxidized for 0, 10, and 100 hrs in 800 degrees C air.
Titulo: The influence of pre-treatment on the oxidation behavior of Co coated SOFC interconnects

Sentencas: The samples were analyzed using FE-SEWEDX, XRD, and XPS before and after 10 and 100 h of oxidation.
Titulo: The influence of pre-treatment on the oxidation behavior of Co coated SOFC interconnects

Sentencas: Significant differences in oxidation behavior were observed.
Titulo: The influence of pre-treatment on the oxidation behavior of Co coated SOFC interconnects

Sentencas: For example, the pre-oxidized samples exhibited combined coating/oxide scales that contained much less Fe and were significantly thinner compared to samples that were not preoxidized.
Titulo: The influence of pre-treatment on the oxidation behavior of Co coated SOFC interconnects

Sentencas: The presence of a continuous chromium oxide layer (from pre-oxidation) may inhibit iron transport from the substrate and thus reduce the thickness of the oxide scale.
Titulo: The influence of pre-treatment on the oxidation behavior of Co coated SOFC interconnects

Sentencas: Possible mechanisms for the observed oxidation behavior are presented and discussed.
Titulo: The influence of pre-treatment on the oxidation behavior of Co coated SOFC interconnects
